{
  "version": "1.0",
  "last_updated": "2026-04-10T18:00:00",
  "notes": {
    "how_to_use": "Each cycle generates two price targets (high_target and low_target) based on 2:1 Gann diagonal projection. The diagonal starts at the cycle high/low and projects forward by 1 cycle duration. Where the diagonal meets the horizontal price level is the 'target_time'. Targets persist across cycles until price reaches them or they are manually marked missed.",
    "when_to_update": "Update prices after each cycle completes: read the cycle high, low, and resulting targets from the GannCycles indicator on TradingView. Mark targets as 'reached' when price hits them, or 'missed' if they expire without being hit. Review at each new cycle boundary.",
    "price_fields": "high_target = upward price destination (from cycle low), low_target = downward price destination (from cycle high). Both are calculated by the GannCycles Pine indicator automatically.",
    "target_time_calc": "target_time = cycle_end + (cycle_end - cycle_start). The target projects forward by exactly 1 cycle duration from the cycle end.",
    "direction_field": "expected_direction is based on cycle type analysis (up/down/continuation/reversal). It indicates which target (high or low) is more likely to be hit."
  },
